  "texts": [
    "Thus, when per-inverter currents are unavailable, a pragmatic approximation can use the pre-fault IED measurements as a proxy for the aggregate inverter contribution and distribute it uniformly across devices.Assuming that: (i) all inverter generations are equal during and previous the fault; and (ii) their positive-sequence injections maintain magnitude and phase angle close to pre-fault values, those assumptions can lead to an approximated form of Equation ( 17) as shown next:V comp (d) = - N k=1    (d -d w,k) Z (1) L I w N, if d w,k < d, 0, otherwise.",
    "(18)where I w is a pre-fault proxy selected consistently with the loop in use.",
    "Thus, Table II enumerates these proxies for the rows of Table I.",
    "It is important to observe that this approximation can estimate the fault distance d using only the IED measurements.IV.",
    "Fig. 6 shows a realistic onshore wind-farm collector network modeled in PSCAD."
  ]
}